<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">

<!-- @pageTitle = Those Eyes -->

<!-- @include "global/head.kit"-->

<body class="project-page">
    <!-- @include "global/header_nav.kit" -->

    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="title-frame margins">
                <h1 class="project-title puzzle-type puzzle-auto" data-vertical-align="bottom">Those Eyes</h1>
                <h5>Prepare to be psychologically thrilled</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="vimeo-video hero-image" id="T1" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/t1.jpg');padding:59.79% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146786058?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="t1_logo-and-movie_v3d">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="tags-frame margins">
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Logo</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Strategy</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Identity</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Posters</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="adjectives margins">
                <p>Mind-bending</p>
                <p>Dissociative</p>
                <p>Grand</p>
                <p>Anxious</p>
                <p>Emblematic</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="intro margins">
            <h5>
                Designing for a film was on our “first-year-in-business” bucket list. When Evan Harris reached out to us about his directorial debut for a psychological thriller, we were&nbsp;ecstatic. 
            </h5>
        </section>
        <section class="content margins" id="those-eyes">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t2_logo-with-collage.jpg" alt="Logo with collage" class="width4" id="T2">
            <div class="width2 under-img">
                <img src="assets/project-pages/t3_logodetail.png" alt="Logo detail" class="width2" id="T3">
                <p class="width2">
                    <span class="italics">Those Eyes</span> follows Steven as he is chased through doors into different worlds by a figure with glowing red eyes. It was important for us to bring the abrupt, forceful clashing of these realities together in a cohesive way through the&nbsp;visuals.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="vimeo-video width6" id="T4" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/t4.jpg');padding:48.48% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146799291?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="t4_logo-iterations-v2">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t5-thoseeyesinstagram-v2.png" alt="Instagram posts" class="width6" id="T5">
            <p class="width6">
                Physical collage was the perfect way to represent jolty interruptions between the different tones and environments in the film and it provides grittiness to the thriller genre. Those Eyes was made completely with practical effects, so the graphics are made practically as&nbsp;well. 
            </p>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t6_abstract-ticket(lg).png" alt="Abstract ticket" class="width3" id="T6">
            <div class="vimeo-video width3" id="T7" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/t7.jpg');padding:100% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146799301?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="t7_collage-gif-final">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t8_posters.png" alt="Posters" class="width6" id="T8">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t9_posterdetail.png" alt="Poster detail" class="width3" id="T9">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t10_posterdetail.png" alt="Poster detail" class="width3" id="T10">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t11_eye-ball-icon.jpg" alt="Eye ball icon" class="width2" id="T11">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t12_brochure.jpg" alt="Brochure" class="width4" id="T12">
            <div class="vimeo-video width4" id="T13" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/t13.jpg');padding:73.87% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146799306?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="t13_image-treatment-demo">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <p class="width2">
                We worked with shots from <span class="italics">Those Eyes</span> to create a custom image treatment that unifies the different worlds and brings forward their intense&nbsp;colors.
            </p>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t14_monster-graphic.jpg" alt="Monster graphic" class="width6" id="T14">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t15_murderer.jpg" alt="Murderer" class="width3" id="T15">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t16_premiere-invitation.jpg" alt="Premiere invitation" class="width3" id="T16">
            <p class="width6">
                Each typeface represents a unique tone from the movie. Just like in the film, they are most dynamic when used in&nbsp;combination.
            </p>
            <div class="vimeo-video width6" id="T17" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/t17.jpg');padding:48.48% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146799322?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="t17_world-premiere">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <p class="width6 narrow-text">
                <span class="italics">Those Eyes</span> is simultaneously a love letter to iconic avant-garde films, a showcase piece for the filmmakers, and a symbolic story for the human&nbsp;experience.

            </p>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/t18_finalimage.jpg" alt="Final image" class="width6" id="T18">
        </section>
        <!-- @include "global/components/next-project.kit" -->
         
        <!-- @include "global/footer.kit" -->


    </main>
    <!-- @import "global/scripts.kit"-->

</body>

</html>